events.description: Monthly report on residential property prices and sales activity in Norway for January 2026.

facts.fact_text: Norway house prices rose by 0.6% month-on-month in January 2026.

evidences.evidence_text: House prices in Norway rose by 0.6% month-on-month in January 2026, after showing no growth in the previous month.

facts.fact_text: Residential sales decreased by 4.4% year-on-year to 8,156 units in January.

evidences.evidence_text: Residential sales totaled 8,156 units in January, 4.4% fewer than the same month last year

facts.fact_text: The number of homes listed for sale increased by 13.2% compared to the previous year.

evidences.evidence_text: 8,490 homes were listed for sale, 13.2% more than a year ago.

facts.fact_text: The average time to sell a home decreased from 71 days in December to 62 days in January.

evidences.evidence_text: The average time to sell a home was 62 days in January, compared to 71 days in December.

facts.fact_text: Yearly house price growth eased to 4.2% in January from 5% in December.

evidences.evidence_text: On a yearly basis, house prices increased by 4.2% in January, easing from a 5% rise in December.
